                    <h1>WCPS Answers Questions About Changes in Instruction, Schedules and Operations Because of COVID-19</h1>
            
      
      
      
      
      
  <div class="region-content">
        <div about="/news/wcps-answers-questions-about-changes-instruction-schedules-and-operations-because-covid-19" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document" class="ds-1col node node-news node-promoted view-mode-full clearfix">

  
  <h2 class="subheading">
<span class="label-inline">Posted </span>April 7, 2020</h2>

<div class="field field-type-text-with-summary">
  
  
                <p><strong>Hagerstown, MD (April 7, 2020)</strong> - Washington County Public Schools (WCPS) has implemented many changes as precautions in the ongoing effort to reduce the spread of the coronavirus. Parents, students, WCPS staff and community members have asked many questions about safety, health, instruction, schedules and more. A website page with answers to frequently asked questions and additional information has been posted and will be updated regularly: <a href="http://wcpsmd.com/school-health/covid-19-faq">COVID-19 FAQ</a>. </p>
